                <h1>Woodrow Wilson: A Glimpse into His Early Life</h1>
                <p>Woodrow Wilson was born on December 28, 1856, in Staunton, Virginia. He grew up in a religious Southern family, influenced by his father, a minister, and his mother, who encouraged his education. Wilson excelled in academics, attending Princeton University. His early life shaped his progressive ideals and passion for reform.</p>
